The article discusses the issue of military spouse unemployment and calls for businesses to make significant changes to address this problem. The author highlights the challenges military spouses face, such as frequent relocations and deployments, and emphasizes the importance of supporting military families for national security. The author proposes creating flexible and remote work opportunities to allow spouses to maintain their careers despite moving frequently. The article encourages businesses to join the Military Spouse Employment Advisory Council and shares the success stories of organizations that have already implemented such initiatives. It concludes by urging readers to take action and create a culture where military spouses can thrive.